title: Daniel Harwi Memorial 28th Annual Lower Providence Spring Classic Crit
description: Daniel Harwi Memorial 28th Annual Lower Providence Spring Classic Criterium
notes:
STATE CHAMPIONSHIPS SPECIAL NOTE:   This year's event has been designated as the 2015 Pennsylvania Cycling Association Junior State Championships for men and women who are 9-10, 11-12, and 13-14.   Non-Pennsylvania riders are invited to all races.

 

Women's 1/2/3 riders:   We are working hard to increase the payout for your field.   Please spread the word to others to please come and support our efforts towards moving in this direction.  

 

Race proceeds benefit:  Crushing Cancer for Chrissy Arrow Karabin for our teammate Tim Karabin and the Hypertrophic Cardiomyopathy Association for Daniel Harwi who we have never forgotten in these 27 years.

 

Hypertrophic Cardiomyopathy Association

 

PARKING UPDATE - ALL RACE Parking is in the same new location as last year on the outside of the course this year. No parking in the center lots you may have grown accustomed to as we've worked with the township to make this race safer and an institution for Lower Providence as they've given us a permanent parking opportunity. Let's not make the businesses in this part resent us by parking in their lots.

Race parking is in a parking lot on the corner of Van Buren Ave and Adams Ave (at turn #4). There are two lots to choose from. The best way is to turn from Audubon Road onto Adams Ave. This will bring into the office park. Proceed to what is turn #4 of the race course. On your left is race parking. 

Also if you are coming in off of Rittenhouse Road, you could turn onto Van Buren Ave and parking will be on your right at the second driveway. Registration will be near start finish and in this lot to keep things compact/easy.  As well, registration will be in this lot to keep things compact/easy.

Please listen to the marshalls when they direct you to the parking location.

As always, this is a PCA / BAR race (www.pacycling.org)

Many thanks to our five sponsors of the event:

 

1.) The Performance Lab powered by the Rothman Institute (www.theperformancelabnj.com)

2.) Caffeinated Cyclist (www.tccyclist.com)

3.) Pennsylvania's Women's Racing Series (www.pawomensracing.blogspot.com)

4.) Lower Providence Township (www.lowerprovidence.org)

5.) Talksoft Corporation (www.talksoftonline.com).

 

Without supporters of this support we'd not have great events to gather and compete at. Please make your support of these sponsors known by going to their websites or storefronts and letting them know you recognize them as a stand-up company who supports what you like to do.  That in itself will provide them with the ROI to continuing to help support cycling events in the Mid-Atlantic.

Couple things to note:

1) This is one of the top three highest attended criteriums in Pennsylvania - (last year had 400+ racers!!!).
2) This is the longest running criterium in the state.
3) All races are designed to be USA Cycling upgrade worthy (As all races SHOULD be)!


Women's events - We have worked hard to ensure that women racers have as many opportunities to race as possible.   We feel that it is important there be a Women's Cat 4 race in addition to the 1/2/3 and W35+ races.   Please be sure to put us on your calendar.

PA Women's Series: a season-long points competition open to all women racers of all ages. Racers do not have to live in PA to participate in the Series.   The Women's PA BAR series is open to PA resident riders only.  For more information, go to pawomensracing.blogspot.com.     
 

Fine Print/Details: 

$5 Late Fee in effect as of 4/12 11:45PM EST (please register by Friday night).
2014 BAR Champions race for free. Email prior to registration and you will be added to the registration. BAR Champions are required to wear their BAR jerseys.
Each additional race is $15 if pre registered, $20 day of the race.
Payout is 1/2 amount listed if <25 racers in event (exceptions-women, juniors).
Race is run rain or shine.
Promoter reserves the right to shorten, combine or alter events as needed due to weather, timing and other uncontrollable circumstances (crash delays, injuries, needs of Police, EMTs, Acts of God).
Course: 1 Mile, Clockwise, Mostly Flat, 4-corner crit with Free Laps/wheel pit. 
Registration opens at 7:15 am.
No aero bars.  Approved helmets must be worn..
All USA Cycling rules apply. 
Entry fee includes insurance surcharge of $2 for USA Cycling & $5 for Citizens. 
Promoter reserves the right to combine or cancel races if less than 12 racers register for an event.
Masters races for Cats 1-4 only.
Directions:  Go to www.mapquest.com and type in directions from your location to the corner of Van Buren Ave & Adams Ave., Norristown, PA 19403

 

For Information: Ken Walsh - woodsretreat@hotmail.com.

title: Rock Lititz Bike Race & Block Party
Rock Lititz Bike Tour
course: Riders have three choices of rides.  20 miles, 30 miles and 62 miles.  All rides start and finish in Lititz Springs Pool, 401 Maple St, Lititz, PA 17543.
registration: Registration is from 7:30 to 9:00 a.m. At the Lititz Springs Pool, 401 Maple St, Lititz, PA 17543. You will receive a cue sheet at Registration.  The courses will be marked.
notes: There will be one rest area in the 20 mile ride and two rest areas on the 40 and 62 mile rides. The courses all travel through beautiful Lancaster County Farmland and they will be marked. Healthy snacks and drinks will be available at the rest areas and the finish.  Each pre-registered rider will receive a Rock Lititz Shirt.   After you complete the ride, you are encouraged to watch the Rock Lititz Bike Races and hear great live music.  There are also food trucks and vendors and activities for the family.  It will be a great day for all.
directions: Lititz Pennsylvania is in Lancaster County PA, about 1.5 hour drive time from Philadelphia and Baltimore and 2 hours 40 minutes from New York City.

title: T-Town Showdown Clinic
description: There will be two collegiate track clinics held at The Valley Preferred Velodrome for the 2015 season, on May 2nd and Sept 5th, prior to the race days of those same weekends. Marty Nothstein and other qualified and experienced racers will guide participants through learning track skills.
course: Marty Nothstein and other qualified and experienced racers will guide participants through learning track skills at the Valley Preferred Cycling Center.
registration:
Registration for the May 2-3 weekend is found: https://www.bikereg.com/t-townshowdown2015

Registration for the Sept 5-6th weekend is found: https://www.bikereg.com/2015trackeasterns
notes: This is a permit for the clinic portion of the above two weekends. There is no racing on may 2nd or sept 5th 2015.
directions:
Getting to the Track
• Philadelphia 1.5 hours
• Harrisburg 1.5 hours
• New York City 2 hours
• Baltimore 2.5 hours
• Washington D.C. 3 hours
• Boston 6 hours

From New York City (Newark airport) or east:
Take I-78 West to Exit 49A (Route 100 South).  Follow Route 100 South past the 3rd traffic light and turn right onto Route 222 South/Route 100 South. Get into the left lane and make a left turn at the next traffic light onto Cetronia Road.  Take the second right turn onto Mosser Road and follow .4 miles to Valley Preffered Cycling Center, located on the left side of the road.

From Philadelphia:
Take I-95 to I-476 North to Exit 56 (Lehigh Valley).  Take Route 22 West and follow to Exit 49A (Route 100 South).  Follow Route 100 South past the 3rd traffic light and turn right onto Route 222 South/Route 100 South. Get into the left lane and make a left turn at the next traffic light onto Cetronia Road.  Take the second right turn onto Mosser Road and follow .4 miles to Valley Preferred Cycling Center, located on the left side of the road.

From Harrisburg, York, or further west:
Take I-83 North to I-81 East. Follow I-81 East until it separates from I-78.  Take I-78 East (Allentown) and follow to Exit 49A (Route 100 South).  Follow Route 100 South past the 3rd traffic light and turn right onto Route 222 South/Route 100 South. Get into the left lane and make a left turn at the next traffic light onto Cetronia Road.  Take the second right turn onto Mosser Road and follow .4 miles to Valley Preferred Cycling Center, located on the left side of the road.

From Scranton and north:
Take the Pennsylvania Turnpike (I-476) to Exit 56 (Lehigh Valley).  Take Route 22 West and follow to Exit 49A (Route 100 South).  Follow Route 100 South past the 3rd traffic light and turn right onto Route 222 South/Route 100 South. Get into the left lane and make a left turn at the next traffic light onto Cetronia Road.  Take the second right turn onto Mosser Road and follow .4 miles to Valley Preferred Cycling Center, located on the left side of the road.

description:
West Chester Cross Classic IV - PACX Race

Bayard Rustin High School
1100 Shiloh Road
West Chester, PA 19382
course: Don't miss the 4th year for this excellent venue.  Consistently rated one of the top cross courses and overall races in the PACX series.  Classic cyclocross course with two sets of barriers and variable terrain mostly grass, with some pavement. The 2.2 mile closed course is great for spectators. Course will be flowing and challenging, making use of natural run-ups, off cambers sections, and lots of cornering. Course is designed by “angry” Bob Reuther, local cross legend and long time advocate of local cycling.
registration:
Pre-registration will be open on bikereg.com until October 16, 2015 11:00PM.

·         There is a $10 late fee for day-of registration.

·         Day of Registration and sign-in will be open at 8AM and will close 30 min prior to each race.

·         A USAC license is required to participate in this race, day-of and annual licenses will be available for purchase at registration.

·         Additional races - only $10!

·         Registration price includes $3 USAC insurance fee.
notes:
This race serves as a fund raiser for Rustin High School Wrestling Team.  A portion of the entry fee proceeds will be donated to the team.

Prizes*:

Men Cat 4/5, Men Masters 55+ merchandise prizes.  Men Cat 3/4  pays $150 5 deep, Women 1/2/3 pays $200 5 deep.  Masters 35+ pays $200 5 deep, Masters 45+ pay $250 6 deep.  Elite men pays $300 7 deep. To better support racers, we have added cash prizes for Cat 3/4 and Masters 45+.
* Note that if field minimums of 20 for the Pro 1/2/3 and 15 for all other cash paying races aren't met, cash prizes will be cut by 50% or to 50% of total entry fees collected. .
directions:
Bayard Rustin High School
1100 Shiloh Road
West Chester, PA 19382

Centrally located…30 minutes from Wilmington DE, Lancaster PA, King of Prussia.  45 minutes from Phila, S. Jersey.  Just off Route 202 – 3 miles south of West Chester PA.

·         Registration will be at tent or inside Rustin High School if weather unfavorable

·       There will be indoor permanent bathroom facilities with showers.

·         Bike wash will be available.

·         We will also have a concession stand set up.  Bring some cash for some goodies and help out a good cause.

Call-up Protocol: 

·         Call-ups will only be awarded by promoter discretion. We will try to utilize current PACX series standings or 2014 final standings.

·         Staging will begin 10 minutes prior to each race

 Lapped Riders:

Lapped riders will finish on the same lap as the leaders. Riders in danger of being lapped must yield to oncoming racers and are not to interfere with their progress or trail behind them.

 Technical Pit:

A double sided pit will be marked and available approximately halfway through the course. If riders enter the pit, they must make some sort of exchange or mechanical adjustment.

Results:

Results will be posted at the registration area. Results will be made final 15 minutes after being posted. Podium, awards, and photos will occur roughly a half hour after each race.

Note:

·         The course will be open for inspection and warm-up at approximately 8:00am.

·         Every racer must have an approved helmet.

·         Mountain bikes will be allowed WITHOUT bar ends.

description:
Cyclocross National's Prep Training Race

WCCX is pleased to announce a Cross National's Prep Training Race on Sunday December 27.  This event will be held on the famed WCCX course at Rustin High School in West Chester, PA. 

Use this opportunity to fine-tune your fitness and ride with others on a great course.  We are charging a nominal entry fee ($10) to cover US Cycling Insurance and provide a donation to the Rustin High School Wrestling Team.  Event will be posted on Bikereg by 12/17.

Start Times: 11:00 Cat 1234 & Masters 50-55 min race, 11:02 Women's, Jrs. and SS 40 min race.  This is a self-seeding event, so place yourself appropriately  The goal of the day is to get in a great workout, follow some fast wheels and stay healthy, so no wheel chopping, aggressive tactics, name calling etc - heckling is ok.

We will also be collecting winter coats for Safe Harbor, a local shelter, so if you get a new one for Christmas bring last years model and we will drop them off after the race.
